fix(status-bar): correct 3 compiler errors in StatusBarService and Control

CS0165 – StatusBarService.SetText: 'frozen' unassigned when _statusBar is null
  - int frozen = 0 initialised before null-conditional IsFrozen call

CS1503 (×2) – IVsStatusbar.Progress expects ref uint, not ref ulong
  - ReportProgress / ClearProgress signatures changed: ref ulong -> ref uint
  - SampleToolWindowControl.xaml.cs: cookie local var ulong -> uint

Date: 2026-03-19
Affects: Services/StatusBarService.cs, ToolWindows/SampleToolWindowControl.xaml.cs

- New `Services/OutputWindowService.cs`: wraps SVsOutputWindow / IVsOutputWindow
  - CreatePane (fInitVisible=1, fClearWithSolution=0) on first load
  - Public API: WriteLine, Log (timestamped), Activate, Clear
  - Thread-safe: switches to UI thread internally via JoinableTaskFactory

feat(status-bar): add StatusBarService wrapping IVsStatusbar

- New `Services/StatusBarService.cs`
  - SetText (with auto-unfreeze), StartAnimation / StopAnimation (SBAI_General)
  - ReportProgress / ClearProgress (progress bar cookie pattern)
  - RunWithAnimationAsync convenience helper for background work

feat(package): wire OutputWindowService and StatusBarService into MyPackage

- MyPackage exposes `OutputWindow` and `StatusBar` singleton properties
- Both services initialized in InitializeAsync before UI-thread switch
- Post-load: writes startup log to Output pane, sets status bar text
- InitializeToolWindowAsync passes services through SampleToolWindowState

feat(tool-window): add Output Window & Status Bar demo buttons to UI

- SampleToolWindowControl.xaml: 5 new buttons grouped by feature section
- SampleToolWindowControl.xaml.cs: handlers use JoinableTaskFactory.RunAsync
  for fire-and-forget async work; no UI thread blocking
- Renamed Button_Click -> Button_ShowVsLocation_Click; removed duplicate handler
- SampleToolWindowState: added OutputWindowService and StatusBarService props

Date: 2026-03-19
Affects: MyPackage.cs, SampleToolWindowState.cs, SampleToolWindowControl.xaml,
         SampleToolWindowControl.xaml.cs, Services/ (new folder, 2 files)
Breaking: SampleToolWindowState gains 2 new properties (non-breaking addition)
